<article class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-white">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-5">
    <div class="prose max-w-none">
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">Many small businesses do not need a huge marketing department. They need a marketing consultant who can look at the full picture and identify the highest-impact next step.</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">You may need a consultant if your marketing feels scattered</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">If you have a website, Facebook page, Google profile, and maybe ads, but none of it feels connected, an internet marketing consultant can turn scattered activity into a simple plan.</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">SEO should be part of the conversation</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">Internet marketing SEO is the foundation for being found over time. SEO internet marketing includes your website structure, local keywords, service pages, reviews, technical basics, and useful content.</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">A consultant helps prioritize budget</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">Not every business should start with paid ads. Some need local SEO first. Others need a better landing page, stronger offer, or clearer tracking before spending more money.</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">The goal is clarity</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">A good consultant should explain what matters, what can wait, and what will move the business closer to calls, messages, appointments, or sales.</p>
      <div class="rounded-3xl p-8 sm:p-10 my-12" style="background:var(--primary-lt)">
        <h2 class="text-2xl mb-4" style="color:var(--primary-dk)">What a consultant should review</h2>
        <ul class="checklist mb-0">
          <li>Your Google Business Profile and local SEO visibility.</li>
          <li>Your website speed, structure, and calls to action.</li>
          <li>Your content and service pages.</li>
          <li>Your ad setup and conversion path.</li>
          <li>Your reviews, reputation, and tracking.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
